opendial.bn.distribs

Class ConditionalTable.Builder

  • java.lang.Object
    • opendial.bn.distribs.ConditionalTable.Builder
  • Enclosing class:
    ConditionalTable

    public static class ConditionalTable.Builder
extends java.lang.Object
    Builder class for the conditional table. The builder allows you to add rows to the table. Once all rows have been added, the resulting table can be created using the build() method.

      • fillConditionalHoles

        public void fillConditionalHoles()
        Fill the "conditional holes" of the distribution -- that is, the possible conditional assignments Y1,..., Yn that are not associated with any distribution P(X1,...,Xn | Y1,...,Yn) in the table. The method create a default assignment X1=None,... Xn=None with probability 1.0 for these cases.

      • isWellFormed

        public boolean isWellFormed()
        Returns true if the probability table is well-formed. The method checks that all possible assignments for the condition and head parts are covered in the table, and that the probabilities add up to 1.0f.
        Returns:
        true if the table is well-formed, false otherwise

      • normalise

        public void normalise()
        Normalises the conditional table

      • build

        public ConditionalTable build()
        Builds the corresponding probability table. If some conditional tables have a total probability mass that is less than 1.0, creates a default None value to cover the remaining mass.
        Returns:
        the corresponding conditional table
